Administrator who cares that the result of curriculum encoder and curriculum-text annotator are digested regularly into the user-interface.
One who writes the ontology specification and encodes it, that one that specifies the abstraction mechanisms to be implemented by the editor developer.
One who designs and develops the topics and competency editor which uses the ontology specification in order to create a usable editor for topics, competencies, and levels related tools.

Developer of the Intergeo platform which uses the metadata specification and ontology structure in order to allow for the appropriate information edition and presentation in the querier and annotator roles. This developer also adapts the indexing, search, and auto-fill interfaces.

The role browsing through a curriculum-text (a standard, a textbook) and create, in the ontology, the needed competencies and topics. This may also require to declare a new learning-pathway, region, programme.

The role of identifying a text of interest that could be shared among intergeo platform users, obtaining an appropriate electronic version, adding hyperlinks into this text linked to the competency and topics web-view, and uploading the document into the platform for further sharing.

Usage of the competency-editing-tool in order to add or edit titles of a competency or topic or descriptions in the own language. Typically such a role requires knowledge of several languages but does not require to understand the data-model of a competency (hence cannot change it).

Usage of the editing front-end of the community platform in order to annotate resources as referencing(?) the given competencies or topics, being made for the given educational-programme, or with many other fields (such as authorships or license).
Usage of the text-search of the platform, or the ontology or curriculum-texts browsing, in order to find relevant resources.
